  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\">\n<p>Congratulations on completing week one! After finishing your lessons you should now know:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>46 Hiragana</li>\n<li>How to count from 1 to 1000 and also how to count yen, things, and floors</li>\n<li>How to introduce yourself, express possession of an object, describe a location and how to categorize something, ask and tell the time</li>\n<li>How to use 13 different grammar points: <ol>\n<li><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Particles ha and mo (は, も)</span></li>\n<li><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Particle ka to express questions and doubts (か)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on kono, sono, ano (この, その, あの)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on nan and dare (なん, だれ)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on no (の) to indicate possession</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\">\n<span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on koko, soko, asoko (ここ, そこ</span><span style='font-family:\"Microsoft Yi Baiti\";'>、</span><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>あそこ)</span>\n</li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on no (の) to categorize something </span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on doko, ikura (どこ, いくら)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particle wo (を), present tense (V-masu) and negative form (V-masen)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particle de (で) and to (と)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on nani (なに)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particles ni, kara, made, goro (に, から, まで, ごろ)</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on past tense (V-mashita)</span></li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">If you have any questions on what you have learned this week, don’t forget that you can always ask for more help in the student community!</span></p><p><a href=\"https://japaneseonline.gogonihon.com/communities/Q29tbXVuaXR5LTI0Mzg=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"../../images/shared/Go_to_community_(1).png\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" srcset=\"../../images/shared/Go_to_community_(1).png?width=1920 1x, ../../images/shared/Go_to_community_(1).png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, ../../images/shared/Go_to_community_(1).png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></a></p>\n<a href=\"../weeks/week1-test.html\" class=\"test-link-card\">\n  <span class=\"test-link-icon\">📝</span>\n  <div class=\"test-link-info\">\n    <h3>Take the Week 1 Test</h3>\n    <p>35 questions covering Days 1–5 · Multiple choice, true/false, fill-in-the-particle, and reading match</p>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"test-link-arrow\">→</span>\n</a>",
